As part of Black History Month celebrations, the White House hosted a virtual roundtable on Black mental health and wellness. The discussion was moderated by Susan Rice and featured Dr. Miriam Delphin-Rittmon, Taraji P. Henson, Sloane Stephens, and Nneka Ogwumike. The participants shared their own mental health challenges, stressed the importance of seeking support and self-care, and discussed efforts by the Biden-Harris Administration to prioritize mental health and diversify the behavioral health workforce. The article encourages anyone experiencing mental health challenges to seek help and provides a helpline and website for more information on treatment options.